title.rendered: Most Popular Prime Day Deals So Far

content.rendered:
Day one of Prime day is officially over and we are now onto the second day. I thought I’d compile a list of the most popular deals so far (I’ve removed any that are no longer available as nobody wants to see something they missed out on).

  1. Amazon Prime: Reload Or Purchase Amazon Giftcard $40+ & Get $10 Credit
  2. Amazon: Use One Citi ThankYou Point & Get $20 Off $50, Works On Giftcards
  3. [YMMV] Amazon: Add Any Debit & Get $25 Promo Credit
  4. Amazon Warehouse 20% Off
  5. Amazon Prime: iHealth Touchless Thermometers From $14.99
  6. [YMMV] Amazon: Smart Plug For $0.99 With Promo Code SMARTPLUG99, SMART10, AMZNPLUG
  7. Amazon Prime: LifeStraw Personal Water Filter For $9.99
  8. Echo Show 8 For $2.49 After Echo Show 1 Trade In
  9. Amazon: Apple AirPods with Charging Case (Wired) For $114.99
  10. Amazon Echo Flex + Free Smart Light Bulb For $9.99/Echo Dot + Free Light Bulb For $18.99

Unsurprisingly the most popular deals so far have been the more general deals, ones that can be used on gift cards or low dollar cost items.

title.rendered: Rakuten.com/eBates: Earn 90% Back On LifeLock (26,721 Amex MR Points For $296.90)

content.rendered:
Update 10/14/20: This is back. Hat tip to Matthew

Contents

  • 1 The Offer
  • 2 Our Verdict

The Offer

Direct link to offer

  • Shopping portal Rakuten/eBates is offering 90% cash back on LifeLock purchases

Our Verdict

Rakuten cashback can be converted into American Express Membership Rewards points. LifeLock Ultimate Plus Plan is the most expensive plan, this will cost $296.90 and you’d earn $267.21 or 26,721 MR rewards points. This works out to be 1.11¢ per point. This turns it into a profitable deal if you cash out via the Charles Schwab Platinum (1.25¢ per point).  New Rakuten members can get another 3,000 points for signing up as well.

Personally this is an easy pass for me, too much room for something to go wrong and I don’t really want to have to deal with that for a very slight profit. Others (especially people that value MR points highly) will find this worth doing.

Hat tip to My Points Life via VFTW

content.rendered:

Contents

The Offer

Targeted offer sent out via e-mail, subject line is ‘Get $10 cash back when you pay touch-free with PayPal’

  • PayPal is offering some users $10 cash back when you make a touch free payment of $10 or more

Our Verdict

Nice deal if you’re targeted, share the subject line if you know it in the comments below.
